content:
import socket
import os

def receive_data(sock):
    try:
        data = sock.recv(1024).decode('utf-8')
        return data
    except UnicodeDecodeError:
        # Handle binary data
        return sock.recv(1024)

def download_file(server_socket, filename):
    with open(filename, 'wb') as f:
        while True:
            data = server_socket.recv(1024)
            if not data:
                break
            f.write(data)

def main():
    host = "s3.greenhackers.org"
    port = 5001

    s = socket.socket()
    s.connect((host, port))

    # 1. Receive the file list from the server
    files_list = receive_data(s)
    print("Available Files:")
    print(files_list)

    # 2. Select a file to download
    selected_file = input("Enter the filename to download: ")
    s.send(selected_file.encode())

    # 3. Receive the file from the server
    download_file(s, selected_file)

    print(f"\nFile {selected_file} downloaded successfully.")

    s.close()

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

title: fileserver5.py

import socket
import os
import threading  # Import the threading module

def handle_client(client_socket):
    # 1. List all files in the current directory
    files_list = list_files_in_current_dir()
    files_str = "\n".join(files_list)
    
    # 2. Send the file list to the client
    client_socket.send(files_str.encode())

    # 3. Receive the selected file name from the client
    filename = client_socket.recv(1024).decode()
    print(f"\nSelected file: {filename}")

    if not os.path.exists(filename):
        print('No such file in Server!, exiting.....')
        client_socket.close()
        return

    # File exists in the server, transferring now...
    print('File exists in Server, Transferring now...')

    with open(filename, 'rb') as f:
        for byte in f:
            client_socket.send(byte)

    print(f'\n\nTotal File Size is {os.path.getsize(filename)} bytes')
    print('File transferred')

    client_socket.close()

def list_files_in_current_dir():
    current_dir = os.getcwd()
    files = [f for f in os.listdir(current_dir) if os.path.isfile(os.path.join(current_dir, f))]
    return files

host = "s3.greenhackers.org"
port = 5001
server = socket.socket()
server.bind((host, port))
server.listen()

print('Server is Listening.....')

while True:  # Keep accepting connections
    conn, addr = server.accept()
    print(f'Accepted connection from {addr}')
    
    # Create a new thread to handle the client
    client_handler = threading.Thread(target=handle_client, args=(conn,))
    client_handler.start()

-- Takes in args from program call, manages em
local arg = { ... } 
if #arg ~= 2 then
    print("Incorrect number of arguments")
    return
end

-- Attempt to establish connection with websocket
local ws = http.websocket(arg[1])
if ws == false then
    print("Invalid websocket address")
    return
end

-- Tell server it is singlular service & get confirmation
ws.send("SINGLE SERVE")
local modeStatus = ws.receive()
if modeStatus ~= "SINGLE SERVE" then
    print("Server denied \"SINGLE SERVE\" connection attempt")
    return
else
    print("Connection mode established")
end

-- Local check for requested file
fs.makeDir("Userscripts") -- If the directory doesn't exist
local requestFile = arg[2]
local reqFilePath = fs.find("Userscripts/" .. requestFile)
local fileHandle
if #reqFilePath == 0 then
    -- Requests file as a new entry for the computer
    ws.send("FILEREQ; " .. requestFile)
    reqFilePath = "Userscripts/" .. requestFile
else
    -- Request file from server as a pre-existing
    reqFilePath = reqFilePath[1]
    fileHandle = fs.open(reqFilePath, "r")
    local metadata = fileHandle.readLine()
    if string.find(metadata, "METADATA") == nil then
        print("Failed to retreive metadata header, check file contents")
        return
    end
    metadata = string.gsub(metadata, "-- METADATA; ", "")
    ws.send("FILEREQ; " .. requestFile .. "; " .. metadata)
end

-- Handle server response
local serverResponse = ws.receive()
--local serverResponse = "-- METADATA; V0.1\nprint(\"Hello world\")"

if serverResponse == "NO FILE" then
    print("Server could not find the file")
    return
elseif serverResponse == "VERSION MATCH" then
    print("Local file matches version on server")
    return
elseif serverResponse == "INVALID REQ" then
    print("Request was invalid")
    return
end

print("Writing to file")
fileHandle = fs.open(reqFilePath, "w") -- Overwrites the current file at locationc
fileHandle.write(serverResponse)
fileHandle.close()

function mine()
    fr = turtle.detect()
    while fr == true do
        turtle.dig()
        os.sleep(.5)
        fr = turtle.detect()
    end
    if fr == false then   
        turtle.forward()
        turtle.digUp()
    end
end

function torch()
    y = k % 8   
    if y == 0 then
        turtle.turnLeft()
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.select(16)
        turtle.place()
        turtle.turnRight()    
    end
end
function ret()
    for j=1,k do
        turtle.back()
    end
end
local run = 0
k = 0

term.write("Length: ")
run = read()

for i=1,run do
    mine()
    torch()        
    k = k + 1
    print(k)
end
ret()

title: PlaneMovement | Lua Script
content:
local TweenService = game:GetService("TweenService")
local RunService = game:GetService("RunService")

local Points = game.Workspace.GameSystem.Points
local Plane = game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane

local NewPoint = 1
local Speed = 20 -- More Speed will break the Player's CFrameHandler

local debounce = false

Plane.PrimaryPart = Plane.Center
Plane:SetPrimaryPartCFrame(Plane.Center.CFrame)

function GetTime(Distance, Speed)
	local Time  = Distance / Speed
	return Time
end

function WeldCargoPlane()
	for i = 1, #Plane:GetChildren() do
		if Plane:GetChildren() [i] ~= Plane.PrimaryPart then
			local Weld = Instance.new("WeldConstraint")
			Weld.Part0 = Plane:GetChildren() [i]
			Weld.Part1 = Plane.PrimaryPart
			Weld.Parent = Plane.PrimaryPart
			
			Plane:GetChildren() [i].Anchored = false
		end
	end
end

function MoveCargoPlane()
	NewPoint += 1 
	
	if not Points:FindFirstChild(""..NewPoint) then
		wait(5)
		NewPoint = 1
		Plane.PrimaryPart.CFrame = Points:FindFirstChild("1").CFrame
		Plane.DoorHandlerPart.CanCollide = false
		Plane.DoorHandlerPart.Transparency = 0.5
		Plane.Light.Color = Color3.new(0, 1, 0)
		game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane.DoorHandlerPart.CanCollide = false
		game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane.DoorHandlerPart.Transparency = 0.5
		game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane.Light.Color = Color3.new(0, 1, 0)
		wait(10)
	end
	
	local NextPoint = Points[""..NewPoint]
	local Distance = (Plane.PrimaryPart.Position - NextPoint.Position).Magnitude
	local Time = GetTime(Distance, Speed)
	
	local TweenInformation = TweenInfo.new(
		Time,
		Enum.EasingStyle.Linear,
		Enum.EasingDirection.Out,
		0,
		false,
		0
	)
	
	local Tween = TweenService:Create(Plane.PrimaryPart, TweenInformation, {CFrame = NextPoint.CFrame})
	Tween:Play()
	Tween.Completed:Wait()
	
	MoveCargoPlane()
	
	Plane.DoorHandlerPart.CanCollide = true
	Plane.DoorHandlerPart.Transparency = 0
	Plane.Light.Color = Color3.new(1, 0, 0)
	
	game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane.DoorHandlerPart.CanCollide = true
	game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane.DoorHandlerPart.Transparency = 0
	game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane.Light.Color = Color3.new(1, 0, 0)
	
end

Plane.DoorHandlerPart.CanCollide = true
Plane.DoorHandlerPart.Transparency = 0
Plane.Light.Color = Color3.new(1, 0, 0)

game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane.DoorHandlerPart.CanCollide = true
game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane.DoorHandlerPart.Transparency = 0
game.Workspace.GameSystem.CargoPlane.Light.Color = Color3.new(1, 0, 0)
wait(1)

MoveCargoPlane()

title: Stairs
content:
function dig1()
    for i = 1, 4 do
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.digDown()
        turtle.down()
    end
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.digDown()
end

function dig2()
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.digUp()
    turtle.up()
    turtle.digUp()
end

function main()
    term.write("How Deep? (Recommend max depth of -58)")
    deep = read()
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.digUp()
    for i = 1, deep do
        dig1()
        dig2()
    end
end

main()

title: stargate address book
content:
local addresses = {
    {input = "MSA", output = "-22-2-11-6-30-33-17-12-", here = true},
    {input = "nether", output = "-1-35-6-31-15-28-32-", here = false},
    {input = "end", output = "-18-24-8-16-7-35-30-", here = false},
    {input = "abydos", output = "-1-17-2-34-26-9-33-", here = false},
    {input = "chulak", output = "-1-9-14-21-17-3-29-", here = false},
    {input = "cavum_tenebrae", output = "-1-34-12-18-7-31-6-", here = false},
    {input = "lantea", output = "-18-20-1-15-14-7-19-", here = false},
}

function listCommands()
    print("Available commands:")
    print("- quit/exit/close")
    print("  -- Returns to the command line.")
    print("- help/commands")
    print("  -- Prints this menu.")
    print("- list/addresses")
    print("  -- Prints all addresses.")
    print("- clear")
    print("  -- Clears the screen.")
end

function listAddresses()
    print("Available addresses:")
    for _, address in ipairs(addresses) do
        print("- " .. address.input .. ": " .. address.output)
        if address.here then
            print("  -- you are here!")
        end
    end
end

function findAndPrintAddress(userInput)
    local lowerInput = userInput:lower()  -- Convert input to lowercase for case-insensitivity
    local found = false
    for _, address in ipairs(addresses) do
        if lowerInput == address.input:lower() then
            print("Address for " .. userInput .. ": " .. address.output)
            found = true
            if address.here then
                print("  -- you are here!")
            end
            break
        end
    end

    if not found then
        print("Unknown address. Type 'list' to see available addresses,")
        print("or type 'help' to list all commands.")
    end
end

print("Stargate address book v1:")
print("Type 'list' to see available addresses.")
print("Type 'help' to see available commands.")

while true do
    local userInput = read():lower()  -- Convert user input to lowercase for case-insensitivity

    if userInput == "quit" or userInput == "exit" or userInput == "close" then
        return  -- Exit the loop and end the script
    elseif userInput == "commands" or userInput == "help" then
        listCommands()
    elseif userInput == "list" or userInput == "addresses" then
        listAddresses()
    elseif userInput == "clear" then
        term.clear()
    else
        findAndPrintAddress(userInput)
    end
end

title: xml parsing and print json with boost property tree
content:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<person>
    <id>12345</id>
    <name>
        <first>Иван</first>
        <last>Иванов</last>
    </name>
    <age>30</age>
    <address>
        <city>Москва</city>
        <street>Улица Примерная</street>
        <zipcode>12345</zipcode>
    </address>
    <contact>
        <email>ivan.ivanov@example.com</email>
        <phone>
            <mobile>123-456-7890</mobile>
            <home>987-654-3210</home>
        </phone>
    </contact>
</person>

//--------------------------------------- CODE ---------------------------------------------------//
#include <iostream>
#include <boost/property_tree/ptree.hpp>
#include <boost/property_tree/xml_parser.hpp>
#include <boost/property_tree/json_parser.hpp>

#include "boost/chrono.hpp"

int TestXmlRead() {
    boost::chrono::system_clock::time_point start = boost::chrono::system_clock::now();

    boost::property_tree::ptree pt;

    try {
        read_xml("text.xml", pt);

        std::string id = pt.get<std::string>("person.id");
        std::string firstName = pt.get<std::string>("person.name.first");
        std::string lastName = pt.get<std::string>("person.name.last");
        int age = pt.get<int>("person.age");

        std::string city = pt.get<std::string>("person.address.city");
        std::string street = pt.get<std::string>("person.address.street");
        std::string zipcode = pt.get<std::string>("person.address.zipcode");

        std::string email = pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.email");
        std::string mobilePhone = pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.phone.mobile");
        std::string homePhone = pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.phone.home");

        std::cout << "ID: " << id << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Name: " << firstName << " " << lastName << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Age: " << age << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Address: " << street << ", " << city << ", " << zipcode << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Email: " << email << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Mobile Phone: " << mobilePhone << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Home Phone: " << homePhone << std::endl;
    } catch (const std::exception& e) {
        std::cerr << "Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }
    boost::chrono::system_clock::time_point end = boost::chrono::system_clock::now();
    std::cout << "XML READ Elapsed time: " << boost::chrono::duration_cast<boost::chrono::milliseconds>(end - start).count() << "ms" << std::endl;

    return 0;
}

int TestXmlWrite() {
    boost::chrono::system_clock::time_point start = boost::chrono::system_clock::now();

    boost::property_tree::ptree pt;
    try{
        read_xml("text.xml", pt);

        boost::property_tree::ptree jsonPt;
        jsonPt.put("id", pt.get<std::string>("person.id"));
        jsonPt.put("name.first", pt.get<std::string>("person.name.first"));
        jsonPt.put("name.last", pt.get<std::string>("person.name.last"));
        jsonPt.put("age", pt.get<int>("person.age"));

        jsonPt.put("address.city", pt.get<std::string>("person.address.city"));
        jsonPt.put("address.street", pt.get<std::string>("person.address.street"));
        jsonPt.put("address.zipcode", pt.get<std::string>("person.address.zipcode"));

        jsonPt.put("contact.email", pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.email"));
        jsonPt.put("contact.phone.mobile", pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.phone.mobile"));
        jsonPt.put("contact.phone.home", pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.phone.home"));

        boost::property_tree::json_parser::write_json("out.json", jsonPt);
    } catch (const std::exception& e) {
        std::cerr << "Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }
    boost::chrono::system_clock::time_point end = boost::chrono::system_clock::now();
    std::cout << "JSON WRITE Elapsed time: " << boost::chrono::duration_cast<boost::chrono::milliseconds>(end - start).count() << "ms" << std::endl;

return 0;
}

int main() {
    TestXmlRead();
    TestXmlWrite();
    return 0;
}

title: so77916663.py

import pandas as pd
import sqlalchemy as sa

df = pd.DataFrame([{'name_county': "Santa Bárbara d'Oeste'"}])

engine = sa.create_engine('sqlite://', echo=True)
tbl = sa.Table('t', sa.MetaData(), sa.Column('name_county', sa.String))
tbl.create(engine)

with engine.begin() as conn:
    q = """INSERT INTO t (name_county) VALUES (:name_county)"""
    for row in df.itertuples():
            conn.execute(sa.text(q), [{'name_county': row.name_county}])

title: Untitled
Diggy Hole
content:
--Turtle Diggy Hole
--------FUNCTIONS---------
 
--size setup
 
function setup()   
    term.write("Length: ")
    len = tonumber(read())
    term.write("Width: ")
    wid = tonumber(read())
    term.write("Depth: ")
    dep = tonumber(read())

    if ((wid % 2 == 1 and dep % 2 == 1)) then
        travel = len - 1
        lenAway = true
    end
    if dep%2 == 1 then
        travel = travel + wid - 1
        widAway = true
    end
    travel = travel + dep -1

    if len * wid * dep + travel - 1 >= fuel then
        willrun = false
    end
end
 
--digs across length 
 
function length()
    count = count + 1
    for i=2,len do
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.forward()
    end
end
 
--left turn
 
function TurnLeft()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.turnLeft()
end
 
--right turn
 
function TurnRight()
    turtle.turnRight()
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.turnRight()
end
 
--determines turn
 
function pick()
    eo = count % 2
    if eo == 1 then
        TurnRight()
    elseif eo == 0 then
        TurnLeft()
    end
end

function down()
    count = (wid)%2
    turtle.digDown()
    turtle.down()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    deep = deep + 1
end

function recall()
    if dep ~= 1 then
        for i = 2, dep do
            turtle.up()
        end
    end 

    if lenAway then
        for i = 2, len do
            turtle.back()
        end
    end

    if widAway then
        turtle.turnLeft()
        for i = 2, wid do
            turtle.forward()
        end
        turtle.turnRight()
    end
end

function mine()
    for i = 1, dep do
        for i=1,wid do
            length()
            if i ~= wid then
            	pick()
            end
        end
        if deep ~= dep then
            down()
        end
    end
    
    
end
 
----------GLOBAL----------
 
len = 0
wid = 0
dep = 0
deep = 1
count = 0
fuel = turtle.getFuelLevel()
travel = 0
willrun = true
widAway = false
lenAway = false
 
-----------MAIN-----------
 
setup()
if willrun then
    mine()
    recall()
else
    print("Not enough fuel!")
end
